li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-45_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-47_">Volunteer staff.</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-48_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-50_">What is covered in emergency first aid at work courses?</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworkonlineefawtrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642679790729-1671523415032.jpg?v=1671523434" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworkonlineefawtrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642679790729-1671523415032.jpg?v=1671523434 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworkonlineefawtrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642679790729-1671523415032_500x.jpg?v=1671523434 320w" width="7360" height="4912" alt="Demystifying emergency first aid at work: All you need to know - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Demystifying emergency first aid at work: All you need to know - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-51_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-52_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-54_">All incidents are covered in emergency first aid at work courses, from minor injuries to life-threatening situations, including:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-xiLah eCXiET pf-55_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-56_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-58_">Roles and responsibilities of a first aider</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-59_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-61_">Contents of a first aid kit</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-62_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-64_">Primary and secondary survey</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-65_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-67_">Emergency life-saving procedures</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-68_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-70_">Blood loss and wound management</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-71_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-73_">Minor injuries and trauma</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-74_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-76_">Medical emergencies.</span></li></ul><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-77_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-79_">How is emergency first aid at work training delivered?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworktrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680352373-1671523414981.JPG?v=1671523463" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworktrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680352373-1671523414981.JPG?v=1671523463 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworktrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680352373-1671523414981_500x.JPG?v=1671523463 320w" width="5530" height="3687" alt="The role of emergency first aid training for managers and employees - Dr Richard Dune -" title="The role of emergency first aid training for managers and employees - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-80_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-81_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-83_">There are many different ways to deliver emergency first aid at work training, including:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-xiLah eCXiET pf-84_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-85_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-87_">E-learning (online courses)</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-88_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-90_">Online webinars</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-91_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-93_">Classroom learning</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-94_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-96_">Video link learning</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-97_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-99_">Online blended learning (combination of eLearning and classroom assessments).</span></li></ul><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-100_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-102_">Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, most training providers have adapted their emergency first aid at work training courses to ensure safety. Ofqual, who regulates first aid qualifications in England, recommended that training providers use blended learning, whereby learners complete their theory training online, then practical assessment via video link or recorded videos of learners completing the practical aspects, for example, primary survey or cardiopulmonary resuscitation.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-103_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-105_">How is emergency first aid training accredited and certified?</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworknearmeukaccreditedefawcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680299530-1671523415013.jpg?v=1671523428" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworknearmeukaccreditedefawcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680299530-1671523415013.jpg?v=1671523428 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/emergencyfirstaidatworknearmeukaccreditedefawcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680299530-1671523415013_500x.jpg?v=1671523428 320w" width="7325" height="3899" alt="From choking to burns: Mastering emergency first aid at work - Dr Richard Dune -" title="From choking to burns: Mastering emergency first aid at work - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-106_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-107_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-109_">Basic emergency first aid awareness courses are accredited by the CPD Certification Services (CPDUK). Ofqual approves emergency first aid at work course syllabus through awarding bodies, such as Training Qualifications UK (TQUK), NOCN and Qualsafe.<br><br>Emergency first aid at work certification must be renewed annually. In the third year, learners must attend the full-day course to meet the current regulatory requirements for first aid training.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-110_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-112_">Why is emergency first aid at work training important?</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/workplacefirstaidtrainingemergencyfirstaidatworkcoursethemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680654227-1671523414477.jpg?v=1671523420" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/workplacefirstaidtrainingemergencyfirstaidatworkcoursethemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680654227-1671523414477.jpg?v=1671523420 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/workplacefirstaidtrainingemergencyfirstaidatworkcoursethemandatorytraininggroupuk1642680654227-1671523414477_500x.jpg?v=1671523420 320w" width="5857" height="3614" alt="Emergency first aid at work: A must-have skill for supervisors - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Emergency first aid at work: A must-have skill for supervisors - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-113_"/